Review.Titre: I only needed the page where our signatures are signed, and I find it unreasonable to pay for a page I don't need or accept.
Review.Contenu: Session ID: a50cf32d-9a9b-11ee-addc-3ca82a232fcaDear Online Notary Center,I recently received my bill for $150 and noticed a charge of $50 for a seal on a blank page. I want to clarify that during the session, I was not informed about this additional cost. I only needed the page where our signatures are signed, and I find it unreasonable to pay for a page I don't need or accept.I kindly request that you review my email and rectify the situation by adjusting the bill accordingly. It is important for the notary to clearly explain any extra charges before proceeding with the service.Thank you for your attention to this matter. I look forward to your prompt response and resolution.

Review.Titre: I was charged for 2 signs and seals…
Review.Contenu: I was charged for 2 signs and seals when in fact it was only 1
My wife signed a 2 page document. I signed the same 2 page document. we were charged for 4 documents, with 2 signatures per document.

The system was very glitchy and wouldn't take the documents I was trying to upload. When it finally did, and I connected with a Notary, I explained that the system was malfunctioning and I only needed one of the documents signed. He said he understood, and to work around the system, he would complete all of them "just in case". After signing, he disconnected and charged me 3x the published amount. After wasting 45 mins to get one signature, I just gave up and paid so I could download the doc.

My signature needed to include my first name and middle name and it took the notary a few times to help me get my signature corrected. Even though I was a single signer on the document, I was charged for three signers, which nearly doubled my fee.  If I could have, I would not have bothered to pay for the session, but I was time constrained. So instead of $25 it was $45. If it happens to you, just start over and save yourself the extra fee. The notary never told me there would be extra fees when fixing my problem. It lined her pockets, though so why disclose.
